Coverage counters are now emitted at call sites of `pragma(inline, true)` functions

Previously, functions marked `pragma(inline, true)` would always show `0000000`
in `-cov` coverage reports even when they were executed, because the inlined
function body was never called as a standalone function at runtime.

Coverage counters are now emitted at each call site where the function is inlined,
so the function's lines correctly reflect how many times they were executed.

This is a partial fix: the `-inline` flag case (issue
$(LINK2 https://issues.dlang.org/show_bug.cgi?id=5848, Issue 5848)) is not yet
addressed.
